00:00:05.160 --> 00:00:09.450
&gt;&gt; Female presenter: Welcome to Authors@Google.
Long one of our most acute

00:00:09.450 --> 00:00:12.190
and insightful novelists, Russell Banks often
examines

00:00:12.190 --> 00:00:15.310
the interesting boundaries between our intention
and our

00:00:15.310 --> 00:00:18.439
actions. With his uncompromising and morally
complex new

00:00:18.439 --> 00:00:24.670
novel, Lost Memory of Skin, the two time Pulitzer
Prize

00:00:24.670 --> 00:00:27.710
finalist is at the peak of his powers. Russell
Banks is

00:00:27.710 --> 00:00:34.850
a prolific writer of fiction. His many books
include

00:00:34.850 --> 00:00:41.270
Continental Drift, Cloudsplitter, The Darling
and the short story

00:00:41.270 --> 00:00:47.440
collection, The Angel on the Roof. The Sweet
Hereafter and Affliction

00:00:47.440 --> 00:00:50.789
have been adapted into feature films. Banks
has won

00:00:50.789 --> 00:00:51.900
numerous awards and prizes for his work. Among
them the

00:00:51.900 --> 00:00:52.900
Guggenheim Fellowship, National Endowment
for

00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:53.900
the Arts Creative Writing Fellowship and the
literature award from the

00:00:53.900 --> 00:00:55.690
American Academy of Arts and Letters. He's
the founding

00:00:55.690 --> 00:01:02.320
president of Cities of Refuge, North American
and the past

00:01:02.320 --> 00:01:06.100
president of the International Parliament
of Writers.

00:01:06.100 --> 00:01:10.410
Please join me in welcoming Russell Banks
today.

00:01:10.410 --> 00:01:11.410
[applause]

