occur in

00:04:39.730 --> 00:04:44.290
reality that I wouldn't be bound by the geography
and the

00:04:44.290 --> 00:04:51.810
history and the demographics and so forth
of the city and

00:04:51.810 --> 00:04:56.270
of the region. That I would be free to leave
things out

00:04:56.270 --> 00:05:00.590
put things in shape it around the needs of
story telling

00:05:00.590 --> 00:05:02.889
because it's a novel first and foremost. It's
a story.

00:05:02.889 --> 00:05:11.120
And I wanted the traditions and the conventions
and the

00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:16.660
discipline and rigor that story telling brings
with it to

00:05:16.660 --> 00:05:19.310
determine what went into the story rather
than the place

00:05:19.310 --> 00:05:23.070
itself. The way investigative journalists
might do it or

00:05:23.070 --> 00:05:27.160
sociologists or documentarian or someone else,
a non-fiction writer would use the material.

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:33.830
And the material is real, too, in a sense
or, I should say, based

00:05:33.830 --> 00:05:36.780
in reality as well. The material that is the
context for

00:05:36.780 --> 00:05:43.580
the story. And I spend 6 months a year in
Miami and the

00:05:43.580 --> 00:05:48.020
other 6 upstate in New York, in the Adirondacks.
So you can imagine which

00:05:48.020 --> 00:05:53.610
six months I spend in Miami. [laughter] And
I have an apartment

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:58.440
down there in Miami Beach that looks out over
Biscayne Bay ; it's over on the bay side.

00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:02.969
It looks over towards the Miami skyline and
mainland.

00:06:02.969 --> 00:06:06.180
And from that, I can see this Julia Tuttel
Causeway which

00:06:06.180 --> 00:06:15.000
Barrier Islands to Miami beach. And about
four years ago

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:20.140
articles started appearing in Miami Herald
and a couple

00:06:20.140 --> 00:06:25.210
other papers about a colony of convicted sex
offenders

00:06:25.210 --> 00:06:31.760
who had served their time in prison and were
now living

00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:37.230
underneath that causeway in a kind of encampment,
a shantytown they had built there and they

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:44.699
had been dropped off there with
the connivance and cooperation of law enforcement

00:06:44.699 --> 00:06:52.700
officials and parole officers and so forth
because of a

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:56.780
regulation which had been passed in Miami
Dade count that

00:06:56.780 --> 00:07:02.100
forbade any convicted sex offender from living
within

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:07.100
2500 feet of anywhere where there were children
are likely

00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:10.320
to have gathered which means schools or playgrounds
or

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:15.280
day care centers or anything of the sort.
And so, there

00:07:15.280 --> 00:07:18.740
was no place therefore for them to live anywhere
in the

00:07:18.740 --> 00:07:23.680
city. And so, they had gathered down there,
sort of like

00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:29.870
trolls under a bridge and outcasts. And it
was -- and I

00:07:29.870 --> 00:07:32.780
could see it from my terrace -- a terrace
in my

00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:38.180
apartment. I could look out and see, this
sort of like a magnet in a

00:07:38.180 --> 00:07:40.590
way. Wow, what must that be like. Talk about
the

00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:43.759
unintended consequences of good intentions.
You end up

00:07:43.759 --> 00:07:52.419
with this situation and you've got, you know,
psychopathic serial rapists and pedophiles

00:07:52.419 --> 00:07:59.030
alongside some poor
old guy who got busted for urinating in a

00:07:59.030 --> 00:08:02.870
parking lot at 3 in the morning
in the morning. He got drunk and got busted

00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:06.699
for indecent exposure, that's a sexual crime.
Or you

00:08:06.699 --> 00:08:11.020
got some 21-year-old kid who had sex with
his high school girlfriend who is under 18

00:08:11.020 --> 00:08:14.600
and that's statutory rape and that's sexual
crime. And

00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:16.960
they're all just thrown together. We make
these

00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:20.270
distinctions between first, second, third
degree sex

00:08:20.270 --> 00:08:26.949
offenses when we prosecute and convict and
sentence a sex offender,

00:08:26.949 --> 00:08:29.870
but after that, they're all lumped together
and they're

00:08:29.870 --> 00:08:34.550
all on the national sex offender registry
online. You

00:08:34.550 --> 00:08:39.429
can click right straight to it. They're there
permanently.

00:08:39.429 --> 00:08:43.809
Their face will pop up, location where they
live, where

00:08:43.809 --> 00:08:48.529
they work etcetera will pop right up when
you click right

00:08:48.529 --> 00:08:53.089
onto any neighborhood in America you want
to go to.

00:08:53.089 --> 00:08:55.839
Thanks to Google, you can --. [laughter] Any
neighborhood

00:08:55.839 --> 00:09:01.350
you want and click on a house or a block as
the kid does

00:09:01.350 --> 00:09:08.230
here. I'll read a little episode where that
takes place. And they're all wearing electronic

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:10.110
anklets so
they're under permanent surveillance with

00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:17.459
a GPS unit attached to make sure they
don't go within 2500 feet of where children

00:09:17.459 --> 00:09:23.399
are gathered and don't leave the county in
terms of their parole as well. So anyhow,

00:09:23.399 --> 00:09:28.699
this is a growing
population of these people that little cluster

00:09:28.699 --> 00:09:35.290
of them in
Miami seem to represent a growing social phenomenon.

00:09:35.290 --> 00:09:39.779
And
that reflected a whole lot of other aspects

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:46.300
of our
society as I began to dig into it. And, because

00:09:46.300 --> 00:09:49.500
I
started doing a lot. I knew nothing about

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:54.029
this world
really at all. So I began to investigate

00:09:54.029 --> 00:09:57.740
different aspects of it. Of just the nature
of the

00:09:57.740 --> 00:10:02.730
crime, for one thing, the psychology of what
may be driving some of these

00:10:02.730 --> 00:10:10.819
crimes and the circumstances that may have
led to some of

00:10:10.819 --> 00:10:11.819
these crimes. These particular range of crimes.
And

00:10:11.819 --> 00:10:15.569
also the legal history regarding these sex
offenders.

00:10:15.569 --> 00:10:22.269
And also the psychology of the rest of us.
You know,

00:10:22.269 --> 00:10:28.480
those of us who shape the laws and regulations
and so

00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:33.529
forth with regard to sex crimes. The fears
that drive us

00:10:33.529 --> 00:10:38.309
to try to protect our children as it were.
Feel that

00:10:38.309 --> 00:10:42.399
they are protected in some secure way. I was
interested

00:10:42.399 --> 00:10:47.190
in finding out as much as I could about that.
And much

00:10:47.190 --> 00:10:52.459
of this led me to the Internet. And Internet
addiction

00:10:52.459 --> 00:10:56.889
among young males particularly and then -- and
that

00:10:56.889 --> 00:11:04.800
connection of that to pornography and pornography
addiction as well. And how the line between

00:11:04.800 --> 00:11:09.589
fantasy and
reality especially as regards our erotic life,

00:11:09.589 --> 00:11:14.329
our sex
lives, sexual behavior and so forth. That

00:11:14.329 --> 00:11:19.120
line has
gradually become erased and replaced by a

00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:24.300
zone more than
a line. And so, that more and more it becomes

00:11:24.300 --> 00:11:27.689
difficult
to know when you pass out of fantasy into

00:11:27.689 --> 00:11:32.250
reality or vice
versa. You drift back into fantasy. And increasingly

00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:36.660
so
many of us are living in that gray zone between

00:11:36.660 --> 00:11:39.589
the two
that our human contact especially our perhaps

00:11:39.589 --> 00:11:44.910
our erotic contact with
each other takes place there, in a digitalized

00:11:44.910 --> 00:11:49.189
format
rather than through our skin. And thus the

00:11:49.189 --> 00:11:55.889
title: Lost the Memory of Skin. And there
are many forms in which we've lost the memory

00:11:55.889 --> 00:12:00.420
of skin our basic form of
connection between each other -- basic form

00:12:00.420 --> 00:12:06.129
of intimacy
is through our skin and how that's being displaced

00:12:06.129 --> 00:12:09.310
and
challenged. Perhaps you people working here

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:14.179
know more of that than most
of the people in the country. But the rest

00:12:14.179 --> 00:12:17.269
of us are, nonetheless,
participating in it. It's part of our ongoing

00:12:17.269 --> 00:12:23.870
condition,
our ongoing lives. So anyhow, the book kind

00:12:23.870 --> 00:12:28.790
of arose out of all
that. Out of that massive material that I

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:32.119
accumulated
without really intending deliberately to write

00:12:32.119 --> 00:12:40.139
a novel,
emerged a character of a kid. And it was called

00:12:40.139 --> 00:12:43.189
"the Kid"
in the novel. He wasn't given -- we never

00:12:43.189 --> 00:12:47.929
know his "real"
name, whatever that is. Everybody has a handle

00:12:47.929 --> 00:12:52.759
anyhow online and
elsewhere and this story. The convicted sex

00:12:52.759 --> 00:13:01.869
offenders
tend to use pseudonyms. Real names, they don't

00:13:01.869 --> 00:13:22.910
want to circulate because you can go online
get their real name and find out they're a

00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:34.180
convicted sex
offender. You don't want to rent them an apartment

00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:43.899
or give them a
job and so forth. You can't discriminate based

00:13:43.899 --> 00:13:48.269
on the
